Use this rule when the user asks you to review PeopleCode, Application Engine SQL/PeopleCode, SQR, Query Manager SQL, or raw SQL written against a PeopleSoft 8.56-era database (PeopleTools 8.5x–8.6x, HRMS/Financials/Campus Solutions on-prem) for correctness — especially anything touching effective dates, joins, keys, or which table/view is queried.

Full instructions: [AGENT.md](./AGENT.md).

This rule is **not** about the Morris PeopleSoft Utilities Chrome extension's own TypeScript source — do not apply it to `src/` code review.
